    <name>
				<text>38.1.2.4 Find k</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>A continuous random variable \(T\) has the following probability density function:<br></p>
<p>\[ f_T(t) = \left\{\begin{array}{ll} 0, &amp; \text{if $t &lt; 0$}, \\ {@a@}({@b@}-t/k), &amp; \text{if $0 \leq t \leq k$}, \\&nbsp;0, &amp; \text{if $t &gt; k$}. \end{array}\right. \]<br></p>
<p>Find the following as whole numbers or as fractions:</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>The constant \(k\) = [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</li>
    <p></p>
    <li> \(\text{E}(T)\) = [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</li>
    <p></p>
    <p></p>
    <li> \(\text{E}(T^2)\) = [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt3]]</li>
    <p></p>
    <p></p>
    <li> \(\text{V}(T)\) = [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt4]]</li>
    <p></p>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_solution">Solution</h4>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>&nbsp;We know that the following must be true for the pdf of our random variable \(T\):<br>\( \displaystyle{\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}} f_T(t) \; dt = 1.\)<br>Thus,&nbsp;<br>\[\begin{align*}\displaystyle{\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} f_T(t) \; dt} &amp; =
        \displaystyle{\int_0^k {@a@}({@b@}-t/k) \; dt} \\ &amp;= \left. {@a*b@}t \right|_0^k - \left.\dfrac{{@a@}t^2}{2k}\right|_0^k\\ &amp; = {@a*b@}k - {@a/2@}k \\&amp; = {@a*b - a/2@}k,\end{align*}\]<br>which implies that \(k=\displaystyle{{@1/(a*b-a/2)@}}.\)</li>
    <p></p>
    <li>Using the value for \(k\), the expectation is calculated by: \[\begin{align*}\text{E}(T) &amp; = \displaystyle{\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}} t f_T(t) \; dt\\ &amp; = \int_0^{{@k@}}&nbsp;{@a@}({@b@}t-{@1/k@}t^2) \; dt\\ &amp;= {@a*b@} \left.\dfrac{t^2}{2}\right|_0^{{@k@}}
        - \left.{@a/k@}\dfrac{t^3}{3}\right|_0^{{@k@}}\\&amp; = {@(a*b*(k^2))/2@} - {@(a*(k^2))/3@}\\&amp; = {@ta2@}.\end{align*}\]</li>
    <p></p>
    <p></p>
    <li>Using the value for \(k\), \(\text{E}(T^2)\) is: \[\begin{align*} \text{E}(T^2) &amp;= \displaystyle{\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}} t^2 \cdot f_T(t) \; dt\\ &amp;= \int_0^{{@k@}}&nbsp;{@a@}({@b@}t^2-{@1/k@}t^3) \; dt\\ &amp;= \left.{@a*b@} \dfrac{t^3}{3}\right|_0^{{@k@}}
        - \left.{@a/k@}\dfrac{t^4}{4}\right|_0^{{@k@}}\\ &amp;= {@(a*b*(k^3))/3@} - {@(a*(k^3))/4@}\\ &amp;= {@ta3@}.\end{align*}\]</li>
    <p></p>
    <p></p>
    <li>Using the above values, the variance \(\text{V}(T)\) is evaluated using the formula: \[\begin{align*}\text{V}(T) &amp;= \text{E}(T^2) - \text{E}(T)^2\\ &amp;= \displaystyle{{@ta3@}- {@ta2^2@}}\\ &amp;= {@ta4@}.\end{align*}\]</li>
    <p></p>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
